    <!--
    ARENA: 2.4m x 2.4m, walls at +-1.2m
    Robot spawns at (0,0) = bottom-left area

    TOP VIEW:
    ┌──────────────────────────────┐  y=+1.2
    │  ★ goals (need S-curve)  ★  │
    │                             │
    │  [PLATE_A──────────]  GAP   │  y=+0.40  gap RIGHT (x > +0.30)
    │                             │
    │  ★ goals (straight OK)  ★  │
    │                             │
    │  GAP    [PLATE_B──────────] │  y=-0.30  gap LEFT (x < -0.20)
    │                             │
    │  🤖 robot (0,0)             │  ← straight path to mid goals OK!
    └──────────────────────────────┘  y=-1.2

    Key design:
    - PLATE_B is LOW (y=-0.30) and only blocks RIGHT side
      → robot can go STRAIGHT LEFT or STRAIGHT FORWARD through left gap
      → short goals in bottom-left quadrant: straight path ✅
    - PLATE_A is MID (y=+0.40) and blocks LEFT side
      → goals above PLATE_A require going RIGHT around it
      → top goals: curved path required ✅
    - Together: robot learns BOTH straight navigation AND avoidance
    -->

